* What/How *

1.3 millions particles are continuously emitted by a moving source. A slight asymmetry in the gravitational field allows for continuous expansion.

-----
* Mint preview / Capture *

Minter will get a 4K PNG (2160x2160px bitmap) and a randomly deterministic infinite generative animation.
The 4K capture is made with 6.2 million particles.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to run on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on square or rectangle screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 ‚Üí 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

- Code written in JavaScript / WebGL / ThreeJS / CuloriJS / GLSL shaders
- Unique random deterministic generative animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Infinite animation

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view (1080x1080 px) ‚Äî limited to 3 captures by session

metadata.name: Glossolalia #124
metadata.description:
This series is ultimately about catharsis. The compositions can be chaotic and maybe even a little messy, but they also can be vibrant and diverse‚Ä¶ which is really what this is trying to celebrate: diversity and expression.

Simply, it‚Äôs about the emotions associated with whatever frees you.

Please see the linked fxtext article (on the main project page) for a more in-depth dissection of the concept. It‚Äôs less of a technical discussion, and more about the experience of the artist, and how it became linked with the feelings they associate with the art.

In live mode:

For higher resolutions, you can append ‚Äú&density=2‚Äù to the url to double the size, ‚Äú&density=3‚Äù to triple, and so on.
(This is highly recommended.)

To adjust grain, you can append ‚Äú&grain=##‚Äù to the url. 40 is the default, and 0 will remove it completely.

metadata.name: Disegnatori #159
metadata.description:
Each disegnatore learns a different portion of a city map, looking at it stroke by stroke and creating a probabilistic Markov model of the sequences of relative angles and distances, tracing the outline of each building in that portion of the map. This way, each disegnatore has a different internal understanding of the city.

It then starts from the middle of the canvas and wanders out, stroke by stroke, probability by probability, trying not to intersect any previously drawn outlines and avoiding the edges of the canvas until a predetermined number of edges have been drawn.

The Markov chain drawing model is created during execution from a text file representation of a city map.

Open live to see your disegnatore drawing or to resize.

metadata.name: GPT-3 and me (free companion mint) #172
metadata.description: Free companion piece to my first Fx(text) article! I have never coded a single line of Javascript in my entire life, yet GPT-3 was able to write the code for this work via my inputs. To read the full article visit: https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/gpt-3-and-me:-a-generative-coding-study

metadata.name: Protein Pelt #127
metadata.description:
An incorrectly placed decimal point led to this pattern. A good friend told me it reminded them of protein structures, I found them to look like animal pelts strewn about.

Each "protein" is made up of 100 pelts, random walking around the canvas from the center. Each "pelt" is made of 5 colors sampled from an array of 84 colors.

Press 's' when in live view to save the image.
